unittest-cpp
------------------------------------------
UnitTest++ is a lightweight unit testing framework for C++. It was designed to
do test-driven development on a wide variety of platforms. Simplicity,
portability, speed, and small footprint are all very important aspects of
UnitTest++. UnitTest++ is ANSI portable C++ and makes minimal use of advanced
library and languages features, which means it should be easily portable to
just about any platform.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-2.0.1-1
  libgcc1-4.9.2-3
  libstdc++6-4.9.2-3
  libUnitTest++-devel-1.4.1+git20150425-1bl1
  libUnitTest++1-1.4.1+git20150425-1bl1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-9-1
  binutils-2.25-1
  cmake-3.1.2-1
  cygport-0.18.1-1
  gcc-core-4.9.2-3
  gcc-g++-4.9.2-3
  libtool-2.4.6-1
  make-4.1-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/unittest-cpp/unittest-cpp

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/unittest-cpp/unittest-cpp.git

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack unittest-cpp-1.4.1+git20150425-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./unittest-cpp-1.4.1+git20150425-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/unittest-cpp-1.4.1+git20150425-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/unittest-cpp-1.4.1+git20150425-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libUnitTest++1-1.4.1+git20150425-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libUnitTest++-devel-1.4.1+git20150425-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

